name: Beautiful home in amazing area!
summary: This large, family home is located in one of Toronto's most vibrant downtown neighbourhoods. The five-bedroom, three-bath house is newly renovated and complete with all the amenities you'll need for a fabulous time in the city.
space: Visit Toronto with this fabulous furnished home as your base! This lovely home is surrounded by gardens in the back and front. Inside, you'll find a large open space with a modern kitchen and bright living and dining room. There are two floors up - a master bedroom with a king-size bed and two kids rooms, each with a single bed. The attic is a private space with a king-sized bed, fold-out single couch and a private deck. The basement is fully-finished with a private room and bath, as well as a playroom with another single couch that doubles as a sleeping space. The house will comfortably sleep 10.  For kids of all ages: we have toys, a very cool tree fort, and many great parks and playgrounds nearby.

name: Downtown Harbourfront Private Room
summary: Guest room in a luxury condo with access to all amenities, a view of downtown Toronto and a private entrance.
space: My husband and I are both artists. I give painting and felting workshops and Larry is a filmmaker. We live in a split-level waterfront condo in downtown Toronto, with a guest room on the 2nd level facing downtown Toronto. The room has a private entrance, an en-suite two piece bathroom, wireless internet, cable TV with DVD player, microwave and a small refrigerator. The tub/shower is located in the main bathroom just outside the guest room door. Guests' amenities include: a roof top salt water pool, sauna, exercise room, recreation room, library, racquetball courts and free guest parking. Our building is next door to the ferry docks and attached by a walkway to the Westin Harbour Castle Hotel where guests can enjoy fine dining or a cup of Starbuck's coffee in the morning. We are located across the bay from Centre island on the south, while a short walk to the north will take you to the financial district, the CN Tower, the Air Canada Centre (concert and sports) Metro Convention Centre,

name: Seaton Village Parlour Bedroom
summary: Comfortable sofa bed in airy main floor parlour.
space: Family of 4 (2 kids)  plus a friendly dog open to having clean, quiet, respectful guests in our home. 1 & 1/2 bathrooms (shared) Great neighborhood, quiet, steps to subway, close to University of Toronto, lots of coffee shops, restaurants, Little Korea No noise after 10pm PLEASE  Sofabed is very comfy, fresh sheets and towels provided (WEEKLY FOR LONG-TERM STAYS) Free WiFi, computer in room No TV in room; No kitchen priveleges Fireplace and Surround Sound system available for use. DOG GETS UP EARLY IN THE MORNING AND MAY BARK.  EARPLUGS PROVIDED FOR LIGHT SLEEPERS.

host_about:
I love travelling and exploring new places, making new friends and really enjoy  getting a feel for the culture of the cities I visit by staying in private residences. Live music and art in my life is a must, but solitude in wild places is also something I need regular doses of. Between trips I am an integrative/naturopathic veterinarian at a large animal hospital.
I am able to travel alone and with my husband more now that my children are getting a bit more independent, but we also travel together as a family.
I treat my hosts homes as I would expect people to treat my home, and  leave everything exactly as I find it.

name: Queen Bedroom close to downtown
space: Nestled in the middle of a quiet residential neighbourhood, this fine home is surrounded by parks, trees and has a warm family that enjoys hosting guests from across the world. We are a 5 min. bus ride away from the closest Toronto Transit (TTC) Subway Station, 2 minutes away from the bus stop and about a 15 to 20 minute commute to downtown Toronto. The ceilings are a little lower, but we're at a bargain price! Now you just can’t beat that anywhere else, can you? :-) Amenities include: - Clean interiors always - Personal bedrooms with sheets and towels provided - Free wireless internet access - Unlimited tea and coffee  - Convenient access to subway and local buses  - Information and directions to nearby attractions  - Parking space may be available (upon request) - Easy access to grocery store (2 min. walk away!) - Extra mattresses (if required) Please feel free to ask any questions by AirBnB messenger! We would be happy to answer them and hope to have you come stay with us :)

notes: * Laundry facilities are available at the premises for $4.00 per load (washing and drying) * We also offer transportation to and from the Toronto International and Domestic Airports at $35.00 per trip when we are available.
transit: * Public transit is conveniently located about a 2 minute walk from the house. The closest subway station is also a 5-10 min. bus ride away.  * There is a car-sharing lot within a 3 minute walk as well
interaction: You are welcome to contact us at any time if they have any questions or concerns. While we may not always be around in person, you will have our contact details at all times!
house_rules: * Guests are requested to leave their shoes at the main entrance of our home to help keep the house clean. * Guests are welcome to come and go as they please, provided they share what their initial time of arrival and time of departure on the final day of their stay with us will be. * Guests are requested to let us know in advance if they will require a taxi ride to the airport to allow for smooth planning. * Guests are welcome to extend their stay with minimal notice, as long as the room is not booked by other guests or being used to host family.  * Guests are requested not to let anyone into our home without letting us know in advance.
host_about:
Welcome to our dwelling place! My wife and I live in Toronto and really enjoy what this city has to offer. A home with clean, well set-up rooms, access to cooking facilities and lots of warmth from it's owners, this is an ideal spot to come and spend some time away from home!

Between 2010 and 2018, we have hosted over 750 individuals and couples from over 100 cities and 50 countries around the world! We would love for you to be our next guest. Whether for a few days, several weeks or a couple of months, we'll do our best to take care of your needs and provide you with a great experience you'll enjoy for a while to come. 

Happy Trails!

Please note: some of the pictures are a little bit dated and we have requested an Airbnb photographer to take new ones. Please let us know if you have specific questions!

name: Executive Studio Unit- Ideal for One Person
summary: Brand new, fully furnished studio basement apartment in artistic Leslieville!  Accepting long term rentals only at this time. This is ideal for someone moving to the city for work or school looking for a fully furnished unit.    Bring your laptop and suitcase and you're set.
space: Brand new, fully furnished studio basement apartment in artistic Leslieville!  Full kitchen with microwave, dishes, pots/pans and cooking utensils.  Includes HD TV, AC, and internet.  Private washroom and washer/dryer.  Single bed and convertible queen size futon/bed.  Access to shared backyard and huge two level deck with BBQ.  Well lit separate entrance.  Tons of green space.  Huge park located directly across the street with a swimming pool, skating rink, children's play area, baseball diamonds and soccer field.  Free street parking.   Close to transit. 15 minutes via streetcar downtown. Located a block from shops, restaurants, and pubs on Queen St. E.   15 min walk to grocery store and gym. 20 min walk to sandy beach.

name: Luxury,Safety, Affordability For Women Travellers!
summary: Summer sublet or monthly in Toronto's best midtown neighb. 100% safe, no crime, elegant and quiet but steps away from hip restaurants, cafes, and the bustle of Yonge St and Mt. Pleasant shops. In a luxury apt building with 24-hr security, rooftop indoor pool, sauna and work-out room! Doctors: few minutes from Mt. Sinai and just a few subway stops from University Ave.
space: SALT-WATER POOL! SAFE, SECURE HIP NEIGHBOURHOOD! WEEKLY FARMERS' MARKET! BREATHTAKING UNOBSTRUCTED VIEW OF TORONTO SKYLINE! TWO INDEPENDENT CINEMAS A WALK AWAY! SOME OF THE BEST AFFORDABLE RESTAURANTS IN THE CITY! SUPER QUIET AND PEACEFUL...Superbly run building has no unemployed, no barking dogs, no music...quiet and elegant! It's the safest neighbourhood in town that's got a great pedestrian culture and everything you could ever want to do- a very cultured and hip area. A lovely old park is outside the doorstep and tons of green space surrounds this urban gem. The strip outside my  apartment has award-winning restaurants--some very cheap--two privately owned historical cinemas that show non-box office movies, organic dry cleaners, 24-hour grocers, health food shops, etc. The subway  is a pleasant few minutes walk away. My apartment also has a piano. There's a pool on the roof, too! There's a superb view of the Toronto skyline from my window.  This apartment can't be beat! 3 months or

neighborhood_overview: Simply the best and safest neighbourhood in T.O.  Bus out front of building or subway a few minutes walk away. Surrounded by coffee shops, restaurants, cinemas and great shopping. The only neighbourhood where you have all this plus tons of green space (lovely old park out front and the "Green Belt" walking trail behind.
transit: The subway is a pleasant few minute walk away and will take you to anywhere in the city. The apartment in a zero crime upscale neighbourhood. No need to worry about walking around at any time of night!
access: The entire studio apartment including lovely balcony! Also, saltwater pool, work-out room, and sauna, barb-b-que on the grounds.
interaction: I'm a touring musician with a house 3 hours away, so I can interact by text and phone and will do so as much as possible  : ) I have a friend in the city who does my meet and greets.
house_rules: For one woman only. For security reasons, no visitors for any length of time. Please respect my privacy and personal belongings. The  security deposit that you pay will be returned pending inspection of the apartment: that the apartment is clean and tidy and all personal property has been safeguarded and is intact.
host_about: There are two things I'm crazy about: music and nature! I'm a university music teacher and I'm also a performer. When I'm not doing music, I'm enjoying nature--either hiking, kayaking or swimming. I love being alone at my cabin in the woods--reading or thinking--and I also love the big city and all the creative energy and culture that can be found there.

name: Downtown Toronto - Waterview Condo
summary: Split level waterfront condo with a breathtaking view of Lake Ontario from the living room and downtown Toronto from the bedroom.
space: Artists' Home With Spectacular Views! If you want to stay in a creative environment, then this is the place for you. We are both artists and filmakers, so be prepared for a casual bohemian apartment filled with paintings, drawings, photography and a host of felt crafts. The kitchen is funky and functional, complete with dishwasher.  The unit is a one bedroom, split-level unit with two bathrooms, one queen size bed in the bedroom and full size futon for your guests. Other amenities include: wireless internet, TV, and DVD player, a roof top salt water pool, sauna, exercise room, recreation room, library, racquetball courts and free parking. Attached by a walkway to the Westin Harbour Castle Hotel, we are located across the bay from Centre Island Park on the south and the financial district on the north, which makes our condo the perfect home base for experiencing the best Toronto has to offer.
